Constitutively activating FLT3 mutations has been found in about 30% of all patients with acute myeloid leukemia (AML). The tested compounds were screened for their ability to inhibit FLT3 kinase activity using Caliper's mobility shift assay (MSA). The assay uses a microfluidic chip to measure the conversion of a fluorescent peptide substrate to a phosphorylated product following separation by electrophoresis. The signature of the fluorescence signal over time reveals the extent of the reaction. The assay uses a microfluidic chip to measure the conversion of a fluorescent peptide substrate to a phosphorylated product following separation by electrophoresis. The signature of the fluorescence signal over time reveals the extent of the reaction. The assay uses a microfluidic chip to measure the conversion of a fluorescent peptide substrate to a phosphorylated product following separation by electrophoresis. The signature of the fluorescence signal over time reveals the extent of the reaction.
